<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="511" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/893.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The following telegram has been received from Consul Livingston: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Revolution receiving support on the frontier from Dominican side
                                    and may be prolonged. Overtures made to me by a friend of
                                    Theodore and by Minister Charles Zamor to attempt an
                                    arrangement. Please ask permission Department of State for me,
                                    with cooperation Commander of <hi rend="italic">Nashville</hi>,
                                    to proceed to Dejabon and Ouanaminthe via Monte Cristi.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>I remarked that this work be attended in perfect accord [sic] as
                            Livingston suggests, as the situation mentioned needs attention.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>